# OpenCrane artifact strategy
# Committed build INPUTS: .opencrane/config.yaml, .opencrane/llmstxt/**, .opencrane/chunks.json
# Committed build ARTIFACTS: .opencrane/embeddings.json (~62MB) + .opencrane/milvus.db (~13MB).
#   They are regenerated ONLY when chunks change (scripts/ensure-index.sh) and committed, so
#   releases pack them straight from the repo instead of re-embedding every time. See AGENTS.md.
# Only the transient Milvus lock files stay ignored:
*.db.lock
.opencrane/**/*.db.lock

# opencrane pack output (built + published in CI, never committed)
.opencrane/pack/

# Runtime logs
.opencrane/fetch_docs.log
*.log

# model / HF caches
.cache/
**/.huggingface/

# python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/

# node (chat function deps / build output, at any depth)
node_modules/
**/dist/

# Local planning docs (superpowers plans/specs) -- never commit
docs/superpowers/
.superpowers/

# Per-topic git worktrees (dev-workflow skill) -- never tracked
.worktrees/
